This project implements Chapter 3 of Ruby/Rails Tutorial

-------------------------------------------------------

Instruction from teacher

New rails project (own code)

cd (change to the project directory or all is lost!)
rails new . -T
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
replace the Gemfile github.com/cs4413/sample_app

Create repository (directly or using git remote)
git remote add origin git@github.com:cs4413/sample_app1.git
git push -u origin master

start rails server in root directory of your project

bring up browse localhost:3000

